com.splunk.cloudfwd

Class EventBatch

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.splunk.cloudfwd.EventBatch

  • public class EventBatch
extends Object
    EventBatch can be used if the caller wants a high degree of control over which Events will get sent to HEC in a single HTTP post. Most of the time, there is no need to use an EventBatch, as it is used inside the connection to gather events together when buffering is enabled on the Connection.
    Author:
    ghendrey
